<subSubSection id="193CF0A0E389DE5096A3ECE82F9BE5F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" type="description">
<paragraph id="70B944196FAB4074B8E7610C24E2E218" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E11B0914F10915A384FA878464E2963" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
<emphasis id="1B3E58545AA85E244D686F7A10946D4F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2F42AE31E727A7FA3800465644FFE6A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
A-C. Body brownish-yellow. Total length 0.97; carapace 0.51 long, 0.35 wide; abdo-men 0.61 long, 0.43 wide. Prosoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D662A25A9460D9DE30666CB19E2DB115" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
D and F): carapace finely reticulate; 4 eyes, white, strongly recurved as seen from above; clypeus high, sloping for-ward, marginally rounded; cephalic part raised, posterior part with large conical projection; chelicerae robust, with small basal projection on anterior surface of paturon and an anterodistal tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="12143989B0992393F8AEC15EAD97F3F3" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
G), cheliceral lamina well developed; labium triangular, blunt distally; sternum finely reticulated, with sparse setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C5836881A6C9FA53C2A47A89B12DC79E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
E). Legs yellowish-orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="281C2B966941B0011546AC4F8D7DCBA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
Opisthosoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F5C4D71E640FA6C86409996347B36103" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
A-C and H): dorsal scutum oval, dimpled with tiny pits, smooth between pits, covered with sparse setae; ventral scutum rugose; perigenital plate absent; postgenital plate (PG) straight, nearly same width as preanal plate (PA), 1/4 of the preanal plate length; preanal plate rectangular, with thick posterolateral corners (PLC) and posteromedial projection (PMP).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="042E4064DF6BF0DCF33D69F8AB42F65C" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
Palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2182129EC606D86DD44747DAE6B6EF07" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7826113" captionText="Figure 3. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male, A-C (light) and D-I (SEM); female, J (SEM) and K, L (light). A left palp, prolateral view; B left palp, retrolateral view; C left palp, dorsal view; D left palp, prolateral view; E left palp, retrolateral view; F left palp, dorsal view; G distal part of bulb, prolateral view; H distal part of bulb, retrolateral view; I distal part of bulb, dorsal view; J genital area, ventral view; K genital area, dorsal view; L genital area, ventral view. Abbreviations: BU = bulb; CY = cymbium; EF = epigynal fold; EM = embolus; FE = femur; IVP = inner vulval plate; PA = preanal plate; PAT = patella; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection; SD = sperm duct; SR = seminal receptaculum; TI = tibia; VD = vulval duct; VS = vulval stem. Scales: A-G, J-L = 0.1 mm; H, I = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680168" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">3</figureCitation>
A-I): femur (FE) approxi-mately 2 times longer than patella (PAT); tibia (TI) not swollen, with dorsal trichobo-thrium distally; cymbium (CY) small, cup-shaped; bulb (BU) long pear-shaped, surface smooth; sper-m duct (SD) broad basally, narrow distally; embolus (EM) short, foot-shaped, strongly sclerotised distally, with small acute tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="241E7CDFC51ED9AE54169AEA59313976" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
<emphasis id="82884446DD7640EC597EA34BBF4D966A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">Female</emphasis>
. Habitus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E1CEABF7857C0F157C6038EC4B53C65C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7826109" captionText="Figure 2. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), female. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/670766" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">2</figureCitation>
A-C. Total length 0.96; carapace 0.44 long, 0.32 wide; abdomen 0.65 long, 0.41 wide. Cephalic part lacking large conical projection, chelicerae unmodified; epigynal fold (EF) distinct; other features as in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7E692926E43FF4511D30A50FA0F4EB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
Genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06D19B34D62F881704A54EB9A2B44CEC" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7826113" captionText="Figure 3. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male, A-C (light) and D-I (SEM); female, J (SEM) and K, L (light). A left palp, prolateral view; B left palp, retrolateral view; C left palp, dorsal view; D left palp, prolateral view; E left palp, retrolateral view; F left palp, dorsal view; G distal part of bulb, prolateral view; H distal part of bulb, retrolateral view; I distal part of bulb, dorsal view; J genital area, ventral view; K genital area, dorsal view; L genital area, ventral view. Abbreviations: BU = bulb; CY = cymbium; EF = epigynal fold; EM = embolus; FE = femur; IVP = inner vulval plate; PA = preanal plate; PAT = patella; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection; SD = sperm duct; SR = seminal receptaculum; TI = tibia; VD = vulval duct; VS = vulval stem. Scales: A-G, J-L = 0.1 mm; H, I = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680168" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">3</figureCitation>
J-L): vulval stem (VS) forming an oval structure, strongly sclerotised; vulval duct (VD) weakly sclerotised, con-nected to translucent, saccular seminal receptaculum (SR); inner vulval plate (IVP) long; central process absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="848E363E155B7BE914F88211D584D995" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BB32E46DB9287B4404CA6B329A44D1F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB951CF11581C51C4AA85F8084AA7AAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EF35CA8527EA04971B1DF57DFA8D9901" authorityName="Shear" authorityYear="1978" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Ablemma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ablemma berryi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berryi">
<emphasis id="047DD5A4ABB110981EE970E1624252A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">Ablemma berryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Shear, 1978 in the large conical projection of male carapace (cf. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92EB77189D110D6BA1C1108801C60DE8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
C and F and 
<bibRefCitation id="A5A23F28DF1011592FEE0B1FB0424CD4" author="Shear, W." journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" pagination="1 - 46" refId="B7825948" refString="Shear, W., 1978. Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae. American Museum Novitates 2650: 1 - 46" title="Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae" volume="2650" year="1978">Shear 1978</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 90), but can be distinguished by the acute tip of the embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="748528E8A57BB3ADBF9FBF6E0B658682" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7826113" captionText="Figure 3. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male, A-C (light) and D-I (SEM); female, J (SEM) and K, L (light). A left palp, prolateral view; B left palp, retrolateral view; C left palp, dorsal view; D left palp, prolateral view; E left palp, retrolateral view; F left palp, dorsal view; G distal part of bulb, prolateral view; H distal part of bulb, retrolateral view; I distal part of bulb, dorsal view; J genital area, ventral view; K genital area, dorsal view; L genital area, ventral view. Abbreviations: BU = bulb; CY = cymbium; EF = epigynal fold; EM = embolus; FE = femur; IVP = inner vulval plate; PA = preanal plate; PAT = patella; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection; SD = sperm duct; SR = seminal receptaculum; TI = tibia; VD = vulval duct; VS = vulval stem. Scales: A-G, J-L = 0.1 mm; H, I = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680168" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">3</figureCitation>
A-I; vs. very long, laminar embolus, see 
<bibRefCitation id="5945E9B9D58DF3E68A795DA2FA01C68E" author="Shear, W." journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" pagination="1 - 46" refId="B7825948" refString="Shear, W., 1978. Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae. American Museum Novitates 2650: 1 - 46" title="Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae" volume="2650" year="1978">Shear 1978</bibRefCitation>
: figs 93 and 94) and the large preanal plate, which is nearly four times the length of the postgenital plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E369B892BC0A4EBA639E373C969268E7" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7826105" captionText="Figure 1. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), male. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Abbreviations: PA = preanal plate; PG = postgenital plate; PLC = posterolateral corners; PMP = posteromedial projection. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/680221" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">1</figureCitation>
H and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6C0F2B498DD4A36DD2B31CE9811A3B4C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7826109" captionText="Figure 2. Ablemma shimojanai (Komatsu, 1968), female. A habitus, dorsal view; B habitus, ventral view; C habitus, lateral view; D prosoma, dorsal view; E prosoma, ventral view; F prosoma, lateral view; G prosoma, anterior view; H abdomen, ventral view. Scales: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85365.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/670766" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365">2</figureCitation>
H; vs. two times the length of the postgenital plate, see 
<bibRefCitation id="5ED5D3C4E95BA6BDF0594DD5E5EA1E23" author="Shear, W." journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="85365" pagination="1 - 46" refId="B7825948" refString="Shear, W., 1978. Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae. American Museum Novitates 2650: 1 - 46" title="Taxonomic notes on the armored spiders of the families Tetrablemmidae and Pacullidae" volume="2650" year="1978">Shear 1978</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 95).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
